      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): backfill provider.model in createWithAdapter when adapter returns empty string",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen a memory embedding provider adapter returns an empty model string,\nthe search index identity is overwritten with `\"\"`, leaving the index\npermanently dirty. This happens during boot when the provider\nregistration races with configuration loading.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n`createWithAdapter` passes the resolved model to the adapter but does not\ninspect the returned `result.provider.model`. If the adapter returns an\nempty string, downstream callers see `\"\"` instead of the resolved model\nname, which corrupts index identity comparison and prevents search from\nworking correctly.\n\nThe fix captures the resolved model before the adapter call and backfills\n`result.provider.model` with it when the adapter returns an empty string.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`extensions/memory-core/src/memory/embeddings.ts`** — store\n  `resolvedModel` and backfill `result.provider.model` when empty\n- **`extensions/memory-core/src/memory/embeddings.test.ts`** — add\n  tests for the backfill case (adapter returns empty) and the\n  already-populated case (adapter returns correct model)\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Unit tests cover both the backfill path (adapter returns `\"\"`) and\n  the preserve path (adapter returns the correct model)\n- The empty-string check (`||`) correctly handles both `\"\"` and `undefined`\n\n## Related\n\nCloses #90042\n参考 #91660 — 相同修复思路，本 PR 含完整 Real behavior proof 和 CI 格式",
        "branch": "fix/issue-90042-Gateway-memory_search-index-st",
